title: LexHealthScores V.2
name: LexHealthScores V.2
description:
**This is a revised edition of the first dataset we uploaded.  Simplified the violations so it would be easier to search.**

Dataset of collected restaurant health inspection scores and addresses for Lexington, KY. NOT COMPREHENSIVE.  Collected and compiled by University of Kentucky students (UKC101/GEO509).

To search for individual restaurants, violations, or recent inspection scores, use the provided filters to highlight your results.  Click on individual points to see all available data about a specific restaurant, or click the "Data" tab at the bottom to see the whole dataset.

Filter violations by selecting Vio## from the Violation filter (## corresponds to the two-digit number of the violation, eg. Vio23).  "yes" implies a violation was found on the most recent inspection, and usually a description of the violation can be found by clicking on the individual restaurant and looking for the description of the violation in question.  

These violations were chosen because they are "critical" violations, and if violated, the restaurant must fix them within a specified period of time and be re-inspected.

Index of Violations:

Violation 01 (Vio01)= SOURCE, CONDITION, NO SPOILAGE

Violation 03 (Vio03)= POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD (SAFE TEMPERATURE)

Violation 04 (Vio04)= FACILITIES TO MAINTAIN PRODUCT TEMPERATURE

Violation 07 (Vio07)= POTENTIALLY HAZARDOUS FOOD NOT RE-SERVED

Violation 11 (Vio11)= PERSONNEL WITH INFECTIONS RESTRICTED

Violation 12 (Vio12)= HANDS WASHED AND CLEAN HYGIENIC PRACTICES

Violation 20 (Vio20)= SANITIZATION RINSE CLEAN, UTENSILS SANITIZED

Violation 27 (Vio27)= WATER SOURCE AND SAFETY

Violation 28 (Vio28)= SEWAGE AND WASTE DISPOSAL

Violation 30 (Vio30)= PLUMBING CROSS CONNECTION, BACKFLOW, SIPHONAGE

Violation 31 (Vio31)= BATHROOM ACCESSIBILITY AND CONDITION

Violation 35 (Vio35)= INSECTS/RODENTS/ANIMAL CONTROL

Violation 41 (Vio41)= TOXIC ITEMS PROPERLY STORED/USED
